def segment_instances(spot_id, num_neighbors,min_instance_size,return_kgr = False):
    '''
    This takes a given TMA spot and segments it using connected components of
    k-neighbors graph computed with num_neighbors; 
    only the cells residing in instances with size greater than min_instance_size are returned
    '''
    
    spot = cells2[cells2['spots']==spot_id]
    nn = NearestNeighbors(n_neighbors=10).fit(spot[['X:X','Y:Y']])
    kgr = nn.kneighbors_graph()


    min_instance_size = 5
    spot_cn_cell_idxs = {}
    spot_inst_assignments = {}
    instance_assignments = {}
    good_instances = {}

    for cn in range(10):        
        idx = np.where(spot['neighborhood10']==cn)[0]
        spot_cn_cell_idxs[cn] = idx
        instance_assignments[cn] = cc(kgr[idx,:][:,idx])[1]
        counts = np.unique(instance_assignments[cn],return_counts=True)
        good_instances[cn] = counts[0][counts[1]>min_instance_size]
        cn_good_inst_idx = np.where(np.isin(instance_assignments[cn],good_instances[cn]))[0]
        good_inst_assignments = instance_assignments[cn][cn_good_inst_idx]
        spot_good_inst_cell_idx = spot_cn_cell_idxs[cn][cn_good_inst_idx]
        
        # this is the pair of index (in the spot) of good cells, as well as their assignments
        spot_inst_assignments[cn] = (spot_good_inst_cell_idx,good_inst_assignments)
    
    if return_kgr:
        return spot, spot_cn_cell_idxs, spot_inst_assignments, kgr
    
    return spot, spot_cn_cell_idxs, spot_inst_assignments
# construct the adj graphs
num_neighbors = 10
min_instance_size = 5

spot_adj_graphs = {}
spot_data = {}


for spot_id in spot_ids:

    spot_data[spot_id] = segment_instances(spot_id,num_neighbors=num_neighbors,min_instance_size=min_instance_size,return_kgr = True)
    spot, spot_cn_cell_idxs, inst_assignments,kgr  = spot_data[spot_id]

    for cn1 in range(10):
        for cn2 in range(cn1):
            e1,e2 = kgr[inst_assignments[cn1][0],:][:,inst_assignments[cn2][0]].nonzero()
            for s,t in set(list(zip(inst_assignments[cn1][1][e1],inst_assignments[cn2][1][e2]))):
                spot_adj_graphs.setdefault(spot_id, nx.Graph()).add_edge( (spot_id,cn1,s), (spot_id,cn2,t))
    


# relabel the spot graphs to be compatible with the MCMC output
neighbors = {}
colors = {}
node_to_idx = {}
idx_to_node = {}
for spot in spot_ids:    
    graph = spot_adj_graphs[spot].copy()
    neighbors[spot] = {}
    colors[spot] = {}
    node_to_idx[spot] = {}
    idx_to_node[spot] = {}
    for i,node in enumerate(graph.nodes()):
        colors[spot][i] = node[1]    
        node_to_idx[spot][node] = i
        idx_to_node[spot][i] = node

    for i,node in idx_to_node[spot].items():
        neighbors[spot][i] = [node_to_idx[spot][t] for _,t in graph.edges(node)]
        
relabeled_spot_adj_graphs = {spot_id: nx.relabel_nodes(spot_adj_graphs[spot_id], node_to_idx[spot_id]) for spot_id in spot_ids}

def count_triples(graph,color):
    counts = {}
    for v in graph.nodes():
        for edge1,edge2 in itertools.combinations(graph.edges(v),2):

            new = sorted([color[edge1[1]], color[edge2[1]]])
            if (edge2[1],edge1[1]) in graph.edges(edge2[1]):
                key = tuple(sorted(new+[color[v]]))
                counts.setdefault(key,set()).add(tuple(sorted([v,edge1[1],edge2[1]])))
            else:
                key = (color[v],tuple(new), '.')
                counts.setdefault(key,set()).add((v, tuple(sorted([edge1[1],edge2[1]]))))

    return {k:len(v) for k,v in counts.items()}


def count_triples_parallel(inputs):
    graph = inputs['graph']
    cols = inputs['col']
    return count_triples(graph,cols)

for spot in tqdm(validation_spots):
    for isom in trips.keys():
        num_mc = len(trips[isom][spot])
        obs_counts = np.zeros(len(obs_trips[spot]))
        samp_counts = np.zeros((len(obs_trips[spot]), num_mc))
        for i,trip in enumerate(obs_trips[spot]):
            obs_counts[i] = obs_trips[spot][trip]
            for idx,j in enumerate(trips[isom][spot]):
                samp_counts[i,idx] = trips[isom][spot][j].setdefault(trip,0)

        enrichment = np.log2(obs_counts+1)[:,None]-np.log2(samp_counts+1)
        autocor = np.vstack([acf(enrichment[i], adjusted = True,nlags = 100, fft = True) for i in range(enrichment.shape[0])])

        g = sns.clustermap(enrichment[:,::10], col_cluster = False,cmap = 'bwr',figsize = (20,5),vmin = -1.5, vmax = 1.5)
        g.ax_row_dendrogram.set_visible(False)
        g.ax_heatmap.set(xticklabels=[], yticklabels = [])
        plt.title(isom + spot)
        plt.show()

        autocor[np.isnan(autocor)] = 0
        autocor[:,0] = 1

        g = sns.clustermap(np.abs(autocor), col_cluster = False, row_linkage= g.dendrogram_row.linkage, cmap = 'Reds',figsize = (20,5), vmax = .3)
        g.ax_row_dendrogram.set_visible(False)
        g.ax_heatmap.set(yticklabels = [])
        plt.title(isom + spot)
        plt.show()

Quantifying autocorrelations¶












In [233]:



    


autocors = {}
for spot in tqdm(trips['set_samples'].keys()):
    for isom in trips.keys():
        num_mc = len(trips[isom][spot])
        obs_counts = np.zeros(len(obs_trips[spot]))
        samp_counts = np.zeros((len(obs_trips[spot]), num_mc))
        for i,trip in enumerate(obs_trips[spot]):
            obs_counts[i] = obs_trips[spot][trip]
            for idx,j in enumerate(trips[isom][spot]):
                samp_counts[i,idx] = trips[isom][spot][j].setdefault(trip,0)

        enrichment = np.log2(obs_counts+1)[:,None]-np.log2(samp_counts+1)
        ac = np.vstack([acf(enrichment[i], adjusted = True,nlags = 100, fft = True) for i in range(enrichment.shape[0])])
        ac[np.std(enrichment,axis = 1) ==0] = 0
        ac[:,0] = 1
        autocors.setdefault(isom, {})[spot] = ac.copy()

    p75[i] = {k:np.percentile(v[:,i],75) for k,v in autocors['set_samples'].items()}

def prep_df(p25,perc):
    df = pd.DataFrame(p25).reset_index().rename({'index':'spot'},axis = 1).melt(id_vars = ['spot'],var_name= 'lag', value_name = 'value')
    df['percentile'] = perc
    return df
    
plot_df = pd.concat([prep_df(p25,'25th'), prep_df(medians,'50th'), prep_df(p75,'75th'), prep_df(maxes,'100th')])

g = sns.catplot(data = plot_df, y = 'value', x = 'lag', hue = 'percentile', dodge = True, height = 5,aspect = 5, s = 2.5)
plt.xlabel('lag',fontsize = 40);

    perm_gp1_counts[perm] = {}
    for trip in total_gp1_good_counts.index.values:
        perm_gp1_counts[perm][trip] = 0
        for spot in good_gp1_counts.columns:
            if spot not in key_choices:
                col = obs_trips[spot]
            else:
                chosen_k = np.random.choice(key_choices[spot])
                col = trips['exact_samples'][spot][chosen_k]
            
            perm_gp1_counts[perm][trip]+= col.setdefault(stringmap[trip],0)
